commit.message:
Also use SLIDE_Y for xdg_popup window

SLIDE_Y and FLIP_Y is actually applied by order, so it is necessary to
apply SLIDE_Y after FLIP_Y if FLIP_Y can not move the window within
screen.

commit.message:
Make Gtk use client unfocus commit.

Client unfocus has the best timing, otherwise we may have weird
behavior, e.g. commit to another window.

I thought it has always been the case for gtk, but looks like gtk im
module has always been using server side unfcous commit.

commit.message:
Change GtkIMContext.reset to always commit preedit. (fcitx/fcitx5-unikey#35)

In Gtk2/Gtk3, also use a hack to monitor mouse click on the widget to
trigger a reset.

This change actually breaks im-keyboard's reset, but seems to be ok for
other because usually reset will be implemented as "clear everything".
So we still won't end up with "double commit" issue.
infamous one and we have sync release schedule.

commit.message:
Seems firefox doesn't like the batch mode call sequence.

ProcessKeyEventBatch is introduced to mainly workaround Gtk4 limitation.
While it does helps and ideally it should work on gtk2, and gtk3,
certain app (namely firefox) doesn't like it. So lets just revert gtk2/3
back to the old behavior, since they have been working well and no one
complain about it. hangul case is tested, gtk3 works well and
fcitx/fcitx5#445 does not happen.

Fix #22
